<PolicyLayout title="Privacy Policy" lastReviewed="July 2025">

<p>
  Hope For Families ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we
  collect, use and look after your personal information when you interact with our website, attend our programmes
  or contact us.
</p>

<h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
<p>
  Hope For Families is a Scottish Charitable Incorporated Organisation (SCIO) registered with the Office of the
  Scottish Charity Regulator (OSCR) under charity number <strong>SC053715</strong>. We are based in Dundee, Scotland
  and are the <strong>data controller</strong> for the personal data we hold about you.
</p>
<p>
  For data protection enquiries, contact us at:
  <a href="mailto:kelechioliora@gmail.com">kelechioliora@gmail.com</a>
</p>

<h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
<h3>Information you give us directly</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Contact information</strong> — name, email address, phone number when you contact us, register for an event or sign up to our newsletter.</li>
  <li><strong>Participation information</strong> — details about your family, children's ages, medical needs or additional requirements when joining a programme.</li>
  <li><strong>Donation information</strong> — if you donate through our website or via JustGiving, we may receive your name and, with your permission, Gift Aid declaration details.</li>
  <li><strong>Volunteer information</strong> — your skills, availability and references when you apply to volunteer.</li>
</ul>
<h3>Information we collect automatically</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Website usage data</strong> — pages visited, time spent, referring website. This is collected anonymously via cookies. See our <a href="/policies/cookies">Cookie Policy</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not collect sensitive personal data (such as ethnicity, health or religion) unless you choose to share it with us and we have a clear reason for processing it.</p>

