<h2>4. Sharing Your Information</h2>
<p>We do not sell or rent personal data. We may share your information with:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Statutory agencies</strong> (e.g., Dundee City Council, Police Scotland) where required to fulfil our safeguarding or legal obligations.</li>
  <li><strong>Funders and commissioners</strong> — anonymised or aggregated data only, to report on the impact of funded activities.</li>
  <li><strong>Service providers</strong> who help us operate (e.g., email platforms, website hosting) — only those bound by confidentiality agreements and UK GDPR obligations.</li>
  <li><strong>HMRC</strong> — Gift Aid declarations where you have authorised us to make a claim.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. How Long We Keep Your Information</h2>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Programme participation records:</strong> Duration of participation + 3 years.</li>
  <li><strong>Safeguarding records:</strong> As required by the Dundee Child Protection Committee — typically until a child's 25th birthday.</li>
  <li><strong>Financial records:</strong> 7 years from the end of the financial year, as required by HMRC.</li>
  <li><strong>Newsletter subscribers:</strong> Until you unsubscribe.</li>
  <li><strong>General correspondence:</strong> 2 years from the last contact.</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Your Rights</h2>
<p>Under UK GDPR you have the right to:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>Access</strong> a copy of the personal data we hold about you.</li>
  <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate or incomplete information.</li>
  <li><strong>Erase</strong> your data (the "right to be forgotten") where we no longer have a legal basis to hold it.</li>
  <li><strong>Restrict</strong> how we use your data while a complaint is being investigated.</li>
  <li><strong>Object</strong> to processing based on legitimate interests.</li>
  <li><strong>Withdraw consent</strong> at any time, where consent is the legal basis we rely on.</li>
  <li><strong>Data portability</strong> — receive your data in a machine-readable format.</li>
</ul>
<p>
  To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:kelechioliora@gmail.com">kelechioliora@gmail.com</a>.
  We will respond within one calendar month.
</p>
<p>
  You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the UK's data protection regulator, the
  <strong>Information Commissioner's Office (ICO)</strong>, at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a>.
</p>

<h2>7. Security</h2>
<p>
  We take appropriate technical and organisational measures to keep your personal data secure, including
  encrypted data storage, restricted staff access and regular security reviews. In the event of a data breach
  that is likely to cause harm to individuals, we will notify the ICO within 72 hours and affected individuals
  without undue delay.
</p>

<h2>8. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
  We may update this policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated review
  date. Where changes are significant, we will notify you by email if you are a registered participant or
  newsletter subscriber.
</p>

